quran[25]{c,v,t,f}:
  79,43,"You have no knowledge to say anything about it."
  79,44,"To your Lord belongs (the knowledge of) the term thereof?"
  79,45,"You (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) are only a warner for those who fear it,"
  80,40,"And other faces, that Day, will be dust-stained."
  80,41,"Darkness will cover them."
  80,42,"Such will be the Kafarah (disbelievers in Allâh, in His Oneness, and in His Messenger Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم, etc.), the Fajarah (wicked evil doers)."
  83,28,"A spring whereof drink those nearest to Allâh."
  83,29,"Verily, (during the worldly life) those who committed crimes used to laugh at those who believed."
  83,30,"And, whenever they passed by them, used to wink one to another (in mockery)."
  84,25,"Save those who believe and do righteous good deeds, for them is a reward that will never come to an end (i.e. Paradise)."
  85,22,"(Inscribed) in Al-Lauh Al-Mahfûz (The Preserved Tablet)!"
  86,16,"And I (too) am planning a plan."
  86,17,"So give a respite to the disbelievers; deal gently with them for a while."
  87,13,"There he will neither die (to be in rest) nor live (a good living)."
  87,14,"Indeed whosoever purifies himself (by avoiding polytheism and accepting Islâmic Monotheism) shall achieve success,"
  87,15,"And remembers (glorifies) the Name of his Lord (worships none but Allâh), and prays (five compulsory prayers and Nawâfil - additional prayers)."
  88,10,"In a lofty Paradise."
  88,11,"Where they shall neither hear harmful speech nor falsehood."
  88,12,"Therein will be a running spring."
  89,7,"Of Iram (who were very tall) like (lofty) pillars,"
  89,8,"The like of which were not created in the land?"
  89,9,"And (with) Thamûd (people), who hewed out rocks in the valley (to make dwellings)? {1}",footnotes:1:{89:9} "And you hew out in the mountains, houses with great skill." [The Qur’ân, Verse 26:149].
  90,1,"I swear by this city (Makkah);"
  90,2,"And you are free (from sin, and to punish the enemies of Islâm on the Day of the conquest) in this city (Makkah).{1}",footnotes:1:{90:2}
  90,3,"And by the begetter (i.e. Adam عليه السلام) and that which he begot (i.e. his progeny)."